chunks.text: ## MAXIMO SELF-PACED TRAINING GUIDE ## INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY TECH TRAINING ## IT Tech Role in Maximo In Maximo, the IT Tech creates Work Orders from Turn In Service Requests to document sanitization of Assets. ## Available Training Resources User Guides, Job Aids and Quick Reference Documents are available on the EAWM Maximo Training Page to help users learn their role and responsibilities in Maximo at their own pace and in a mode that best fits their learning style. - · User Guides provide the greatest amount of detail on each topic. User Guides include a high-level summary, detailed step-by-step instructions with screen captures, and a Business Process Model mapping out the activities performed by each affected Functional Community. User Guides can be found in the 'Training Materials by Role' section of the Training page, under via links to the Functional Community and Role name. - · Job Aids target critical functionality in Maximo. These documents are intended to be brief and focus

Role' section of the Training page, under via links to the Functional Community and Role name. - · Job Aids target critical functionality in Maximo. These documents are intended to be brief and focus on key issues, highlighting essential steps. These are found in the 'User Documentation' section of the Training page. - · Quick Reference Documents (QRDs) include step-by-step work instructions, in simplest terms. Unlike Job Aids and User Guides, QRDs normally do not include screen captures. These are also posted in the 'User Documentation' section. In addition to the items available on the Training page, this Self-Paced Training Guide directs you to short video demonstrations recorded and narrated by Maximo Instructors as they walk through the steps of completing specific tasks in Maximo. To train for your role, read the appropriate User Guide, Job Aid and/or QRD for a given topic to gain an understanding of the process. Also, watch the video demonstrations as noted below.

To train for your role, read the appropriate User Guide, Job Aid and/or QRD for a given topic to gain an understanding of the process. Also, watch the video demonstrations as noted below. Continue reviewing this information until you are ready to start working in Maximo. IMPORTANT! Please DO NOT attempt to practice any of the steps in the Maximo Production system. If, after reviewing the materials, you are still uncomfortable with working in Maximo, contact your Maximo Site Lead for additional guidance. ## MAXIMO SELF-PACED TRAINING GUIDE ## 1. Asset Turn In Work Order An Asset Turn In Work Order is created form an Asset Turn In Service Request. Once the Work Order is created and completed, the ISO will be notified to certify the Asset(s) sanitization. Sanitization of the Asset(s) is completed by the Responsible Tech and depending on your local business process, verified by a Supervisor. If authorized, a Tech can verify sanitization.

Sanitization of the Asset(s) is completed by the Responsible Tech and depending on your local business process, verified by a Supervisor. If authorized, a Tech can verify sanitization. Key points to remember are that once work is completed, the Work Order must be in the Status of COMPLETE and the associated Service Request in the Status of WSAN (Waiting on Sanitization). These two factors will enable the ISO to be notified, allowing them to certify the Asset(s) have been sanitized. - · To read the User Guide on this topic, please go to the Information Technology Asset Management Training Materials page; under the IT Tech tab, select the Asset Turn In User Guide to download the file. - · To see a demonstration of using Maximo to sanitize an asset, please go to the EAWM Maximo Video Demos.
